STEVE Sodiya, a professional film editor and multimedia expert, is currently being eyed by giant streaming platform, Netflix. Sources confirmed to The Nation that the streaming giant is looking at working with Sodiya on a series of production ahead of 2023.   Aso believes working hard will leave huge legacy in the…     Cremate my body when I die – Femi Kuti     Ritual killings don’t produce billionaires –…   Sodiya, who has 32-years experience in the Nigerian film and television industry, is a top player on the scene. He has worked with top filmmakers that include Kunle Afolayan, Kemi Adetiba, Tunde Kelani amongst others. The Nation contacted Sodiya for comments on the claims that he’s currently on the radar of Netflix and he neither agreed nor denied the claims. In his words, “I am in the dark and I can’t confirm anything for you because I have a working relationship with Netflix owing to my professional relationship with Kemi Adetiba on King Of Boys. But all I can tell you is that I am working on a series of projects this year and will be busy for a better part of 2022 if not the entirety of 2022.”